  "prompt": "Who is Margaret Hill Morris?",
  "response": "Margaret Hill Morris was an important American Quaker and patriot during the American Revolutionary War. She lived in Burlington, New Jersey, and is known for her diary and her support of the American revolutionary cause. During the war, she provided aid and shelter to American soldiers and kept detailed records of the events happening around her. Her diary is considered a valuable historical document that provides insights into life during the Revolutionary period.",
